<section xml:id="nsx-import-third_party"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.1"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
 <title>Third-Party Import of VMware NSX-v Into &o_netw; and
 Neutronclient</title>
 <para>
  Steps to import the NSX-v &o_netw; core-plugin into &lcm;:
 </para>
 <procedure>
  <step>
   <para>
    The packages below are required for the third-party import into the
    &o_netw; venv:
   </para>
   <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      vmware_nsx
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      vmware_nsxlib
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      tooz
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </itemizedlist>
  </step>
  <step>
   <para>
    The packages below are required for the third-party import into the
    neutronclient venv:
   </para>
   <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      vmware_nsx
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      vmware_nsx
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      tooz
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      python_openstackclient
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      keystoneauth1
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      python_glanceclient
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      python_cinderclient
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      oslo.utils
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      openstacksdk
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      deprecation
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      jsonpatch
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      jsonpointer
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      python_novaclient
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      pyOpenSSL
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      cryptography
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      cffi
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      pycparser
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      asn1crypto
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      ipaddress
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      warlock
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      jsonschema
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      functools32
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      httplib2
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      voluptuous
     </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      tenacity
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </itemizedlist>
  </step>
  <step>
   <para>
    If any of the <filename>.whl</filename> files cannot be found in either the
    &o_netw; venv or the neutronclient venv (this is likely the situation in
    this example), you will need to build them on a system (VM is OK).
   </para>
   <substeps>
    <step>
     <para>
      Install the Git and <literal>virtualenv</literal> Python package if they
      are not already installed.
     </para>
     <screen>&prompt.sudo;sudo zypper install git-base
&prompt.sudo;pip install virtualenv</screen>
    </step>
    <step>
     <para>
      Set up a <literal>virtualenv</literal> in the directory
      <filename>/tmp/stage</filename> and install <literal>wheel</literal>, if
      not already done:
     </para>
     <screen>&prompt.ardana;mkdir /tmp/stage
&prompt.ardana;cd /tmp/stage
&prompt.sudo;virtualenv venv
&prompt.sudo;. venv/bin/activate
&prompt.sudo;pip install wheel</screen>
    </step>
    <step>
     <para>
      Build the <filename>.whl</filename> files for
      <literal>vmware-nsx</literal> (Pike release, version 11.0.0) and all its
      dependencies:
     </para>
     <screen>&prompt.sudo;./venv/bin/activate
&prompt.ardana;git clone https://git.openstack.org/openstack/vmware-nsx --branch 11.0.0
&prompt.ardana;rm -rf nsx-whls
&prompt.ardana; mkdir nsx-whls
&prompt.sudo;pip wheel --wheel-dir nsx-whls vmware-nsx</screen>
    </step>
    <step>
     <para>
      Now the <filename>.whl</filename> files of <literal>vmware-nsx</literal>
      and all its dependent packages (except for
      <literal>vmware_nsxlib</literal>) are in the
      <filename>/tmp/stage/nsx-whls</filename> directory.
     </para>
    </step>
    <step>
     <para>
      Build the <filename>.whl</filename> files for
      <literal>vmware-nsxlib</literal> (Pike release version 11.0.0):
     </para>
     <screen>&prompt.ardana;git clone https://git.openstack.org/openstack/vmware-nsxlib --branch 11.0.0
&prompt.ardana;rm -rf nsxlib-whls
&prompt.ardana;mkdir nsx-whls
&prompt.sudo;pip wheel --wheel-dir nsxlib-whls vmware-nsxlib
&prompt.sudo;deactivate</screen>
    </step>
    <step>
     <para>
      Now the <filename>.whl</filename> files for
      <literal>vmware-nsxlib</literal> are in the
      <filename>/tmp/stage/nsxlib-whls</filename> directory.
     </para>
    </step>
   </substeps>
  </step>
  <step>
   <para>
    Copy the <filename>vmware</filename> directory to
    <filename>~/third-party/</filename> directory.
   </para>
   <screen>&prompt.ardana;cd ~/openstack/ardana-extensions/
&prompt.ardana;cp -R vmware ~/third-party/</screen>
   <para>
    Copy the required <filename>.whls</filename> files for the &o_netw;
    <literal>venv</literal> into the third-party area:
   </para>
   <screen><?dbsuse-fo font-size="0.70em"?>
&prompt.ardana;cd /tmp/stage/nsx-whls
&prompt.ardana;cp vmware_nsx-*.whl ~/third-party/vmware/venvs/vmware-neutron/whls/
&prompt.ardana;cp tooz-*.whl ~/third-party/vmware/venvs/vmware-neutron/whls/
&prompt.ardana;cd /tmp/stage/nsxlib-whls
&prompt.ardana;cp vmware_nsxlib-*.whl ~/third-party/vmware/venvs/vmware-neutron/whls/</screen>
  </step>
  <step>
   <para>
    Copy the required <filename>.whls</filename> files for the
    <literal>neutronclient</literal> <literal>venv</literal> into the
    third-party area:
   </para>
   <screen>&prompt.ardana;cd /tmp/stage/nsx-whls</screen>
   <para>
    And then copy the necessary files
   </para>
   <screen>&prompt.ardana;cp <replaceable>FILE_NAME</replaceable>* \
   ~/third-party/vmware/venvs/vmware-neutronclient/whls/</screen>
   <informaltable>
    <tgroup cols="5">
     <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="20*"/>
     <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="20*"/>
     <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="20*"/>
     <colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="20*"/>
     <colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="20*"/>
     <thead>
      <row>
       <entry>
        <para>
         <replaceable>FILE_NAMES to copy</replaceable>
        </para>
       </entry>
       <entry namest="2" nameend="5" align="center"></entry>
      </row>
     </thead>
     <tbody>
      <row>
       <entry><para>vmware_nsx-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>tooz-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>python_openstackclient*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>keystoneauth1-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>python_glanceclient-*.whl</para></entry>
      </row>
      <row>
       <entry><para>python_cinderclient-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>oslo.utils-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>openstacksdk-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>deprecation-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>jsonpatch-*.whl</para></entry>
      </row>
      <row>
       <entry><para>jsonpointer-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>python_novaclient-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>pyOpenSSL-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>cryptography-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>cffi-*.whl</para></entry>
      </row>
      <row>
       <entry><para>pycparser-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>asn1crypto-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>ipaddress-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>warlock-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>jsonschema-*.whl</para></entry>
      </row>
      <row>
       <entry><para>functools32-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>httplib2-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>voluptuous-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para>tenacity-*.whl</para></entry>
       <entry><para></para></entry>
      </row>
     </tbody>
    </tgroup>
   </informaltable>
  </step>
  <step>
   <para>
    Run the third-party import playbook:
   </para>
   <screen>&prompt.ardana;cd ~/openstack/ardana/ansible
&prompt.ardana;ansible-playbook -i hosts/localhost third-party-import.yml</screen>
  </step>
 </procedure>
</section>
